." Manpage for LISTEN4KEYWORD.
.Dd 07 Nov 2016
.Dt "LISTEN4KEYWORD" "67" "Arc Utilities Library"
.Sh NAME
.Nm listen4keyword
.Nd toggles 'listen for keyword' in spoken commands
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility uses the AppleScript engine
to toggle the 'listen for keyword' feature in macOS's
spoken commands tool. This option makes the computer listen
out for the specified keyword, allowing the user to
use spoken commands without having to press any keyboard
shortcuts. This utility toggles this feature without the user
having to open System Preferences and finding the relevant
check box.
.Sh SEE ALSO
arcman(67), osascript(1)
